verses.text_plain: And afterward Moses and Aaron went in, and told Pharaoh, Thus saith the Lord God of Israel, Let my people go, that they may hold a feast unto me in the wilderness.
verses.verse_html: 1And afterward Moses and Aaron went in, and told Pharaoh, Thus saith the Lord God of Israel, Let my people go, that they may hold a feast unto me in the wilderness.

tokens.text: that they may hold a feast

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh said, Who is the Lord, that I should obey his voice to let Israel go? I know not the Lord, neither will I let Israel go.
verses.verse_html: 2And Pharaoh said, Who is the Lord, that I should obey his voice to let Israel go? I know not the Lord, neither will I let Israel go.

verses.text_plain: And they said, The God of the Hebrews hath met with us: let us go, we pray thee, three days’ journey into the desert, and sacrifice unto the Lord our God; lest he fall upon us with pestilence, or with the sword.
verses.verse_html: 3And they said, The God of the Hebrews hath met with us: let us go, we pray thee, three days’ journey into the desert, and sacrifice unto the Lord our God; lest he fall upon us with pestilence, or with the sword.

verses.text_plain: And the king of Egypt said unto them, Wherefore do ye, Moses and Aaron, let the people from their works? get you unto your burdens.
verses.verse_html: 4And the king of Egypt said unto them, Wherefore do ye, Moses and Aaron, let the people from their works? get you unto your burdens.

tokens.text: unto them, Wherefore do ye, Moses

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh said, Behold, the people of the land now are many, and ye make them rest from their burdens.
verses.verse_html: 5And Pharaoh said, Behold, the people of the land now are many, and ye make them rest from their burdens.

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh commanded the same day the taskmasters of the people, and their officers, saying,
verses.verse_html: 6And Pharaoh commanded the same day the taskmasters of the people, and their officers, saying,

verses.text_plain: Ye shall no more give the people straw to make brick, as heretofore: let them go and gather straw for themselves.
verses.verse_html: 7Ye shall no more give the people straw to make brick, as heretofore: let them go and gather straw for themselves.

verses.text_plain: And the tale of the bricks, which they did make heretofore, ye shall lay upon them; ye shall not diminish ought thereof: for they be idle; therefore they cry, saying, Let us go and sacrifice to our God.
verses.verse_html: 8And the tale of the bricks, which they did make heretofore, ye shall lay upon them; ye shall not diminish ought thereof: for they be idle; therefore they cry, saying, Let us go and sacrifice to our God.

tokens.text: upon them; ye shall not diminish

verses.text_plain: Let there more work be laid upon the men, that they may labour therein; and let them not regard vain words.
verses.verse_html:
9Let there more work be laid upon the men, that they may labour therein; and let them not regard vain words. ▼
▼ Let there…: Heb. Let the work be heavy upon the men

tokens.text: therein; and let them not regard

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Let there…: Heb. Let the work be heavy upon the men
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Let there…: Heb. Let the work be heavy upon the men

verses.text_plain: And the taskmasters of the people went out, and their officers, and they spake to the people, saying, Thus saith Pharaoh, I will not give you straw.
verses.verse_html: 10And the taskmasters of the people went out, and their officers, and they spake to the people, saying, Thus saith Pharaoh, I will not give you straw.

verses.text_plain: Go ye, get you straw where ye can find it: yet not ought of your work shall be diminished.
verses.verse_html: 11Go ye, get you straw where ye can find it: yet not ought of your work shall be diminished.

verses.text_plain: So the people were scattered abroad throughout all the land of Egypt to gather stubble instead of straw.
verses.verse_html: 12So the people were scattered abroad throughout all the land of Egypt to gather stubble instead of straw.

verses.text_plain: And the taskmasters hasted them, saying, Fulfil your works, your daily tasks, as when there was straw.
verses.verse_html:
13And the taskmasters hasted them, saying, Fulfil your works, your daily tasks, as when there was straw. ▼
▼ your daily…: Heb. a matter of a day in his day

footnotes.body_text: ▼ your daily…: Heb. a matter of a day in his day
footnotes.body_html: ▼ your daily…: Heb. a matter of a day in his day

verses.text_plain: And the officers of the children of Israel, which Pharaoh’s taskmasters had set over them, were beaten, and demanded, Wherefore have ye not fulfilled your task in making brick both yesterday and to day, as heretofore?
verses.verse_html: 14And the officers of the children of Israel, which Pharaoh’s taskmasters had set over them, were beaten, and demanded, Wherefore have ye not fulfilled your task in making brick both yesterday and to day, as heretofore?

verses.text_plain: Then the officers of the children of Israel came and cried unto Pharaoh, saying, Wherefore dealest thou thus with thy servants?
verses.verse_html: 15Then the officers of the children of Israel came and cried unto Pharaoh, saying, Wherefore dealest thou thus with thy servants?

verses.text_plain: There is no straw given unto thy servants, and they say to us, Make brick: and, behold, thy servants are beaten; but the fault is in thine own people.
verses.verse_html: 16There is no straw given unto thy servants, and they say to us, Make brick: and, behold, thy servants are beaten; but the fault is in thine own people.

verses.text_plain: But he said, Ye are idle, ye are idle: therefore ye say, Let us go and do sacrifice to the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 17But he said, Ye are idle, ye are idle: therefore ye say, Let us go and do sacrifice to the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Go therefore now, and work; for there shall no straw be given you, yet shall ye deliver the tale of bricks.
verses.verse_html: 18Go therefore now, and work; for there shall no straw be given you, yet shall ye deliver the tale of bricks.

verses.text_plain: And the officers of the children of Israel did see that they were in evil case, after it was said, Ye shall not minish ought from your bricks of your daily task.
verses.verse_html: 19And the officers of the children of Israel did see that they were in evil case, after it was said, Ye shall not minish ought from your bricks of your daily task.

verses.text_plain: And they met Moses and Aaron, who stood in the way, as they came forth from Pharaoh:
verses.verse_html: 20And they met Moses and Aaron, who stood in the way, as they came forth from Pharaoh:

verses.text_plain: And they said unto them, The Lord look upon you, and judge; because ye have made our savour to be abhorred in the eyes of Pharaoh, and in the eyes of his servants, to put a sword in their hand to slay us.
verses.verse_html:
21And they said unto them, The Lord look upon you, and judge; because ye have made our savour to be abhorred in the eyes of Pharaoh, and in the eyes of his servants, to put a sword in their hand to slay us. ▼
▼ to be…: Heb. to stink

tokens.text: because ye have made our savour

footnotes.body_html: ▼ to be…: Heb. to stink

verses.text_plain: And Moses returned unto the Lord, and said, Lord, wherefore hast thou so evil entreated this people? why is it that thou hast sent me?
verses.verse_html: 22And Moses returned unto the Lord, and said, Lord, wherefore hast thou so evil entreated this people? why is it that thou hast sent me?

verses.text_plain: For since I came to Pharaoh to speak in thy name, he hath done evil to this people; neither hast thou delivered thy people at all.
verses.verse_html:
23For since I came to Pharaoh to speak in thy name, he hath done evil to this people; neither hast thou delivered thy people at all. ▼
▼ neither…: Heb. delivering thou hast not delivered

footnotes.body_text: ▼ neither…: Heb. delivering thou hast not delivered
footnotes.body_html: ▼ neither…: Heb. delivering thou hast not delivered
